{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Chocolate Cake","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Lightly grease a baking dish and line with baking paper."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites and 80 g sugar in mixing bowl then whip <nobr>5-6 min\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>. Transfer whipped egg whites to a large bowl and set aside.","Place chocolate and hazelnuts in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter and heat <nobr>2 min 30 sec\/70°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add egg yolks and 80 g sugar then mix <nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Gently fold chocolate mixture with spatula into reserved whipped egg whites until fully mixed. Pour cake batter into prepared baking dish and bake for 35 minutes (180°C) or until a cocktail stick inserted in centre comes out clean. Allow to cool completely before icing (approx. 1 hour). Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Ganache","content":["Place chocolate, cream and black food colouring in mixing bowl then melt <nobr>2-3 min\/45°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["Place a serving platter upside down over the cooled cake and carefully invert cake onto platter. Carefully remove baking dish and peel off baking paper. Trim cake as needed with a sharp knife for straight edges.","Evenly spread ganache on top of cake and down the sides with a palette knife. Decorate according to tastes (see tip) and allow ganache to set before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Chocolate Cake","content":["8 egg whites, from large eggs","160 g sugar","280 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa solids), small pieces or callets","140 g hazelnuts","280 g unsalted butter, soft, plus extra for greasing","10 egg yolks, from large eggs"]},{"title":"Ganache","content":["200 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa solids), small pieces or callets","180 g whipping cream","1 ½ tsp black food colouring"]}],"id":"r252596","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-wwHI2gZ0YXo\/XZWqhm